label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 198: De simplicibus
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Disbound manuscript of compilation of simples (medicines made from one component) in 85 chapters with lists of plants for general medical functions and for treating specific parts of the body. Includes lists and passages not present in the edition of the work published in Basel in 1585.
        Language: Latin
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: Parchment, 21 leaves; 1¹⁸(-1) 2⁴; [1-34, 1-8], modern pagination in pencil, lower inner corners.
        Layout: Written in 2 columns of 46 lines.
        Script: Written in Gothic script by a single hand.
        Decoration: 2-line initials, rubrication, and paragraph marks in red, with later additions of blue, green, or black penwork; concluding lists (p. 1-4 [=p. 35-38]) are also decorated with these later colors.
        Binding: 
        Origin: Written in Spain between 1350 and 1380.
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 198
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5316107 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5316107
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs198.html
